Requires:
Python >= 2.7
--:netifaces
--:python-twisted

Summary:
A simple file transfer program that requires zero configuration. It discovers peers through IP Multicast and requires no central server to manage all connections. All communication is purely P2P.

About Modules:
LPDoL:-
Stands for Local Peer Discovery over LAN. All peers are registered on a single multicast group.
Whenever a new peer joins the network it broadcasts a HOOK message